==Awards and nominations==
{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Ricardo Arjona}}
In 1993, he received the Rafael <U+00C1>lvarez Ovalle Order from the then [[President of Guatemala]], [[Ramiro de Le<U+00F3>n Carpio]], for his international accomplishments.<ref name="Merit">[http://www.webcitation.org/67nxeUyC7"Arjona en proceso de "Metamorfosis""]. El Occidental. Archived from[http://www.oem.com.mx/eloccidental/notas/n2466002.htm the original]. Retrieved on April 29, 2012.</ref> At USAC a library hall bears his name.<ref name=cosme/> His birthplace, [[Jocotenango]], named a street after him.<ref name="Biograf<U+00ED>a de Ricardo Arjona">[http://www.ricardo-arjona.net/Biografia.aspx "Biograf<U+00ED>a de Ricardo Arjona"]. Ricardo-Arjona.net. Retrieved on 23 March 2012.</ref>
